            "abstractNote": "Abstract\n            \n              We do not have a complete knowledge of the bat species presence in West Central Brazil domain and still do not understand how bats respond to the ecosystems rapid vanishing. We quantified bat diversity in the Parque Estadual de Terra Ronca (PETER), a Cerrado protected area. Additionally, we report an extension of the\n              Hsunycteris thomasi\n              distribution known only in the Amazon and the western portion of Brazil. Over 1.440 m\n              2\n               h of mist netting and five nights of automatic recording, we recorded five families and 38 species, while the Jackknife first-order estimator predicted the occurrence of 25 species. Besides the register of species for the area, the novelty is the increase in the potential distribution area of\n              H. thomasi\n              in Norwest’s and north of the Midwest of Brazil. We also report the presence of at least one\n              Lonchophylla dekeyseri\n              population, an endemic to Cerrado. The lack of bat captures within the cotton plantation suggests the impoverishment of the bat assemblages due to the extensive loss of native habitats.",
